een and golden robes. A crown of twigs, vines, and leaves sat nicely upon her divine head.<br>
<br>
She watched the City of Amazons with a small smile on her face. <p>~*-:¦:-*~Gaia: Greek Goddess of Earth~*-:¦:-*~ <BR>-§Mother Earth§-¤Mother of the Titans¤-¥Mother of All Creation¥-</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 297<br> <font color=#8A2BE2>(5/31/02 1:01:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.uvic.ca/grs/bowman/myth/images/haifa/h89.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ~Mother Earth~</span><hr size=1> The sound of his deep voice rolled like a thunderstorm as Poseidon appeared beside Gaia. He looked down on the city of Sarmatia with his grandmother. <br>
<br>
&quot;You look happy Mother Earth. Do these people bring you your happiness?&quot;<br>
<br>
His brown curls fluttered in the breeze as Gaia's did and his eyes rested on the pretty goddess. <p>Poseidon~Lord of the Deep Blue Sea~Patron Of Horses And Sailors~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugaiaofearth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gaia of Earth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#8A2BE2>(6/4/02 4:37:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Poseidon</span><hr size=1> Her head turned sending her red curls flying. Her orbs fell upon the Sea God.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hello, Grandoson.&quot;<br>
<br>
She let her hues fall back on the city.<br>
<br>
&quot;In a way they do, Poseidon, they live with a unity that no other Nation of Empire has been able to break. Not even the gods broke their sisterhood. They are a strong people.&quot;<br>
<br>
She let out a content sigh as she watched the lives of the Amazons fold out before her. She turned her head oncer more looking at Poseidon.<br>
<br>
&quot;We, as Gods, have not been able to break that unity. We can't even achieve a unity like that. Always, The God of Olympus bicker and carry on and we sometimes forget that we are family....Yet most of these Amazons are not even distantly related, and they carry on as a family in a circle unborken.&quot;<br>
<br>
With a wave of her hand a grand throne like chair appeared behind her, she sat down crossing her legs and placing her divine hand into her lap.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh dear Grandson, Though all my times I've seen many things. I created those People down there, yet I created Rhea and Chronos too.&quot;<br>
<br>
She did not create the Amazons directly but closely enough. She thought maybe somewhere inside her and all the gods, there was a unity just like the Amazons had just pleading to come out. <p>~*-:¦:-*~Gaia: Greek Goddess of Earth~*-:¦:-*~ <BR>-§Mother Earth§-¤Mother of the Titans¤-¥Mother of All Creation¥-</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 300<br> <font color=#8A2BE2>(6/5/02 10:00:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.uvic.ca/grs/bowman/myth/images/haifa/h89.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poseidon</span><hr size=1> Poseidon quiet and at ease heard the earth goddess out while looking over the lands of which he hardly had any knowledge of. At his summons a huge cloud hovered over to them to block the intense lights of the sun from beaming down on them. <br>
<br>
&quot;Gaia perhaps you have been spending to much time among these mortals to realize that we Olympians are a complete and understanding family. We frely express our inmost feelings and thus all things are out in the open so that we can deal with how we feel amongst each other. It may seem bad, the constant arguing but underneath the tension there is unity.&quot;<br>
<br>
He looks at Gaia, &quot;Maybe you should come home and remember who you really are.&quot;<br>
<br>
A nice cooling breeze passed through qnd sighed in the grass. <p>Poseidon~Lord of the Deep Blue Sea~Patron Of Horses And Sailors~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugaiaofearth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gaia of Earth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#8A2BE2>(6/5/02 3:37:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Home</span><hr size=1> Gaia stared down at the Amazon City for a moment then brought her green orbs back up to her grandson.<br>
<br>
&quot;Home. Maybe I should return home...I have been so busy lately that I havent had any time at home. I'm going to go visit Demeter for a while.&quot;<br>
<br>
She let out a sigh as a whirl of green and grey surrounded her and her throne, when the lights were gone so was The Earth Goddess. <p>~*-:¦:-*~Gaia: Greek Goddess of Earth~*-:¦:-*~ <BR>-§Mother Earth§-¤Mother of the Titans¤-¥Mother of All Creation¥-</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 301<br> <font color=#8A2BE2>(6/5/02 8:43:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.uvic.ca/grs/bowman/myth/images/haifa/h89.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Home</span><hr size=1> As Gaia left the God remained alone on hat hill top over-looking the amazon tribe. The clouds burst forth and rain fell down on the thick grass and flowers in that one spot on the hill, all else was sunny. The water ran down his skin in rivulets and his hair stuck to his head in a wet mop. Poseidon laughed to himself and seemed to walk through an invsible door as he vanished from sight. <p>Poseidon~Lord of the Deep Blue Sea~Patron Of Horses And Sailors~</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm8.showPrevMessage?topicID=143.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm8.showNextMessage?topicID=143.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"